      "id": "5f3e3c7d-351a-4f18-9b93-c56480233294",
      "created_at": "2026-03-17T17:05:07.761Z",
      "response": "🌿 **Doshas** are the three fundamental bio-energies in Ayurveda that govern all physical and mental processes:\n\n1. **Vata** (Air + Space) — Movement & creativity\n2. **Pitta** (Fire + Water) — Transformation & digestion\n3. **Kapha** (Earth + Water) — Structure & stability\n\nEveryone has a unique combination (Prakriti). When doshas go out of balance (Vikriti), health issues arise. The goal of Ayurveda is to restore your natural balance through diet, lifestyle, and herbal remedies."
    },
    {
      "user_id": "4e019e9d-618b-4745-88e7-921dc3ce3918",
      "message": "Yoga for stress",
      "id": "38603d81-b88e-4622-8324-22b932c954ed",
      "created_at": "2026-03-17T17:06:28.368Z",
      "response": "🧘 **Ayurvedic Stress Management:**\n\n• **Pranayama:** Practice Nadi Shodhana (alternate nostril breathing) — 5 min daily\n• **Herbs:** Ashwagandha, Brahmi, Jatamansi are excellent adaptogens\n• **Abhyanga:** Daily warm oil self-massage calms the nervous system\n• **Meditation:** Start with 10 minutes of silent sitting\n• **Routine:** Follow a consistent daily routine (Dinacharya)\n• **Warm bath:** Add a few drops of lavender oil\n• **Diet:** Avoid caffeine, eat warm, nourishing foods\n• **Exercise:** Gentle yoga, walking in nature"
    },
